Review: Takes every element that made the original a fantastic movie and dumbs it down to get some asses in the seats. I picture this playing on FX in the middle of the day when i was sick in middle school and I probably would have loved it.

Review: I find it hard to review this film without comparing it to the 1984 version. While I would not say that movie is a bad visual interpretation of the first Duke book, it's very heavy handed. This version hits the nail much more on the head. The Harkonnen's feel extremely dark without going completely overboard. The Freman and the Gom Jabbar fit what I was picturing when I read the book for the first time. Everyone pictured things slightly differently…
